OL,3,CMore Guernsey islanders are making the
OL,4,Cswitch to full-fat milk
OL,6,F"The two motivations for changing are
OL,7,Fconcerns about hidden sugars in more
OL,8,Fprocessed lower-fat foods and
OL,9,Fpreferring the taste of full-fat
OL,10,Fproducts."
OL,12,FDespite this, low-fat (blue carton)
OL,13,Fmilk remains the most frequently
OL,14,Fconsumed across Guernsey.
OL,16,FThe survey also found that nine out of
OL,17,Ften islanders still regularly drink
OL,18,Flocally-produced milk.
